# Cursor Rules for Synvo API Documentation Project

## Project Overview
This is a Next.js documentation website for Synvo API, built with Fumadocs UI. The project provides comprehensive API documentation with interactive examples and theme-aware components.

## Key Technologies
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- Fumadocs UI for documentation
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- React

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── app/                    # Next.js app router pages
│   ├── (home)/            # Home page and playground
│   ├── docs/              # Documentation pages
│   └── api/               # API routes
├── components/            # React components
│   ├── ui/               # UI components
│   └── theme-aware-image.tsx  # Theme-aware image component
└── lib/                  # Utility functions

content/docs/1.0/         # Documentation content (MDX files)
public/assets/            # Static assets (images, GIFs)
```

## Important Files
- `src/app/(home)/page.tsx` - Main homepage with theme-aware GIF demo
- `src/components/theme-aware-image.tsx` - Component for switching between dark/light mode images
- `content/docs/1.0/` - All documentation content in MDX format
- `public/assets/` - Contains synvo_api_dark.gif and synvo_api_light.gif

## Theme System
- The project supports both dark and light modes
- Uses `synvo_api_dark.gif` for dark mode and `synvo_api_light.gif` for light mode
- Theme switching is handled by the ThemeAwareImage component using `prefers-color-scheme`

## Development Guidelines
- Use TypeScript for all new components
- Follow the existing component structure
- Maintain theme consistency across all UI elements
- Use Fumadocs UI components when possible
- Keep documentation in MDX format in the content/docs/ directory

## Important: Code-Only Focus
- **NEVER run build, dev, or any execution commands**
- Focus only on writing and editing code
- User handles all running, building, and testing
- Provide code solutions without executing them

## API Documentation Structure
The API docs are organized in content/docs/1.0/synvo-api/ with sections for:
- File management
- Context generation layer
- Session & feedback management
- Authentication
